# GitHub Linguist language overrides.
#
# These ONLY affect the language bar / stats shown on github.com. They do not
# change how anything is compiled (the build is C11/gnu11 -- see setup.py).
#
# Why this file exists:
#   - `.h` is ambiguous (C / C++ / Objective-C). Linguist's classifier often
#     mislabels plain-C headers as C++, which made the repo report C++.
#   - `.inc` defaults to PHP in Linguist, but every .inc here is a `*.c.inc`
#     C source fragment #included into a translation unit.
#   - `.v` is ambiguous (Coq / Verilog / V); ours are Coq proofs in verify/.

*.c   linguist-language=C
*.h   linguist-language=C
*.inc linguist-language=C
*.v   linguist-language=Coq
